

//Notes for BG Gradient task: Margit's solution

/**
 * make sure the utf-8 charset is enabled
 * <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
 * 
 * You can use google Material Icons for the arrow icons.
 * input type for arrow buttons: best to use radio buttons, so that only one can be selected at a time. 
 * 
 * give colours a default starting value, or else they will be black.
 * 
 * 
 * linear gradient: you can use the values to define directions, eg -"to bottom left"
 * label for is important to add. 
 * 
 * It's better to use an element for a query selector than an id, because id names might change.
 * 
 * selecting the nodelist representing gradient direction: 
 * let direction = document.querySelectorAll('input[name="direction"]')
 * 
 * 
 * CSS: make the radio button display invisible, and style the label instead. How labels work: they make the whole area clickable. 
 */